registerdb:Field.registerdb:Description:
LLR_RX ack ctlos send mode:
0-regularly return ACKs;
1-regularly return ACKs, but one package will only return one ACK

Average transmission bytes per clk, Used for CTLOS send (LLR_TX, LLR_RX and CBFC_RX):
800G, default value is 800/8/1.25=80 bytes;
400G, default value is 400/8/1.25=40 bytes;
200G, default value is 200/8/1.25=20 bytes;
100G, default value is 100/8/1.25=10 bytes.

A configuration for the maximum permitted value of outstanding_seq.
Values: 0 to 524,288
The absolute maximum permitted value for outstanding_seq_max is 524,288, which is equivalent to consuming half of the total sequence number space.
800G: 3072-12k/128 = 2976;
400G: 1536-12k/128 = 1440;
200G: 1536-12k/64 = 1344;
100G: 1536-12k/32 = 1152.

A configuration for the maximum permitted value of outstanding_data.
This SHOULD be set to the bandwidth delay product for the link to ensure correct operation of the pause and PFC mechanisms.
800G: 2976, byte_res is 128B;
400G: 1440, byte_res is 128B;
200G: 1344, byte_res is 64B;
100G: 1152, byte_res is 32B.

A configuration for the period for CC_Update packet generation by the sender.
Values: 1us to 250ms, resolution is 1 clk.
800G: 64 / (800/8*0.01%) = 6400 ns, *1.25 = 8000 clks;
400G: 64 / (400/8*0.01%) = 12800 ns, *1.25 = 16000 clks;
200G: 64 / (200/8*0.01%) = 25600 ns, *1.25 = 32000 clks;
100G: 64 / (100/8*0.01%) = 51200 ns, *1.25 = 64000 clks.
